						               													<description>Rules Summary&amp;#10;Before the game, players decide what the stakes will be. The object of the game is to score 10,000+ points. Players take turns rolling the dice and have to score points every roll. If they don't, they BAFA and lose all the points they gained that turn and whatever the stakes were to stay in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the first person gets past 10,000 points, all players get one more turn and then the player with the most points after 10,000 is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From back of box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BAFA is the fast paced game of chance that swept the entire Roman Empire. The game was played by everyone, from the Roman foot soldier and the lowly house slave to Caesar himself. Nero and Ghengis Khan both rolled BAFA for coins, for slace and property, for clothing at Roman orgies or just for fun.&amp;#10;Welcome and prepare yourself for the excitement and the adrenaline rush as the world of ancient Rome comes back to life when you play BAFA.&amp;#10;Whatever stakes you decide to play for, one thing is for certain, a great time and great fun await you and your friends as you discover this ancient game of chance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Let the games begin...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
